The paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques for analyzing personality traits from visual data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the subjective nature of data labeling and evaluation, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for personality analysis, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of datasets and challenges for pushing research in the field, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
